17/01/2003
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic said Thursday (16 January) that former President Milan Milutinovic will surrender to The Hague tribunal within days. He confirmed reports that the Yugoslav and Serbian governments have guaranteed his provisional release on bail, given chronic heart problems. While in office, Milutinovic was immune from prosecution. His term expired at the end of December. (Reuters, AP, AFP, Radio B92 - 16/01/03)
